For the arm dynamics, velocities are derived by progressing from one link to the next with the same methodology as used for the vehicle, while joint forces and torques are determined from the force relationships starting from the end-effector and moving down to the base. The bond graph is drawn from the base of the link to the end-effector based on the kinematics of the link. The link inertia elements are attached at the CG velocity port of links in the bond graph. Kinematics relationships are calculated starting from the base (i.e. i = 0) and moving up to the end-effector (
i = l − 1
).

